                            <comment id="14281088" author="acoz" created="Sat, 17 Jan 2015 01:09:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;On second thought, just adding the parentheses won&apos;t work; the +1 needs to come after the division not before.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14281091" author="iamaleksey" created="Sat, 17 Jan 2015 01:10:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Already ninja-fixed in a follow-up commit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14281107" author="JIRAUSER308715" created="Sat, 17 Jan 2015 01:24:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Pretty sure this is wrong now from a range movement consistency standpoint. Why did we change the old formula?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14281113" author="iamaleksey" created="Sat, 17 Jan 2015 01:32:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We throw if pending &amp;gt; 2, so it shouldn&apos;t be an issue there (&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/cassandra-2.0/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/service/StorageProxy.java#L325&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/cassandra-2.0/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/service/StorageProxy.java#L325&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14281114" author="JIRAUSER308715" created="Sat, 17 Jan 2015 01:33:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah the only issue was pending &amp;gt; 1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
